A4.text: Dutch is the native language of most of the population of the Netherlands and Flanders (which includes 60% of the population of Belgium).

A5.text: It is spoken alongside Dutch in the province of Friesland.

A6.text: West Frisian is one of the two official languages in the Netherlands, the other being Dutch.

A7.text: Most Frisian speakers live in the Netherlands, primarily in the province of Friesland.
